                <div id="team-formation" class="col-md-8 col-md-offset-0 list">
                    <h2 class="medium">Team Formation</h2>
                    <ul>
                        <li>
                            Each team should have minimum of 3 and maximum of 5 team members. This is very important.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Each team should have people playing two different roles &ndash;
                            <ul>
                                <li><strong>Champs</strong>&ndash; those who knows how to create something such as
                                    writing code or making maps. The technical person role.
                                </li>
                                <li>
                                    <strong>Hustlers</strong>&ndash; those who can plan, ideate, present, design etc.,
                                    In other words, the non-technical role.
                                </li>
                            </ul>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            We recommend, 1 hustler and 2 champs if you're 3 in size or 1 hustler and 3
                            champs if you're 4 in size. But one non coder is mandatory.
                        </li>
                        <li id="sec-office-stay">
                            Also, it is mandatory for all teams to stay in office during the Knockathon event till Saturday's
                            Presentation. Ladies who are
                            willing to stay in office during the night are welcome. But if they prefer to hack from home, that
                            is fine too.
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </div>

                <div id="registration-process" class="col-md-8 col-md-offset-0 list">
                    <h2 class="medium">Registration Process</h2>
                    <ul>
                        <li>
                            Once the registration desk opens on Friday, 7th Sept at 6:30 PM, you and your team
                            will submit a form with your team names and their roles, Github repo name to keep your code
                            or any other files.
                        </li>

                    </ul>
                </div>


                <div id="rejection-criteria" class="col-md-8 col-md-offset-0 list">
                    <h2 class="medium">Rejection Criteria</h2>
                    <ul>
                        <li>
                            Knockathon starts on Friday, 7th Sept at 6:30 PM and ends on Saturday at 06:30 PM
                            . Any code
                            committed into your Github repo after 10:00 PM Saturday will be rejected for your final build.
                            But there can be extreme cases. You may want to find legitimate reasons to convince the
                            Knockathon team.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            During the concept demo on Saturday Morning, we merely look for some scribbled designs on a
                            paper. Don't waste
                            your time on making PPT or some neat design. However, if you don't have any solid idea, you
                            can also provide the options you have in front you. <p><br/>In case, your idea collides with
                                someone's or a rip-off of some well-known app it will be rejected or advised to change.
                            </p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            During the event, it is mandatory for team members (<a href="#sec-office-stay">except for
                                ladies</a>) to stay in office. If found otherwise, it may be a reason for rejection. Also,
                                ladies can leave the office between 08:00 PM, Friday to 08:00 AM, Saturday only.
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </div>

                <div id="presentations" class="col-md-8 col-md-offset-0 list">
                    <h2 class="medium">Presentations</h2>
                    <ul>
                        <li>
                            There will be three presentations &ndash;
                            <ul>
                                <li><strong>Idea Presentation</strong> &ndash; An hour after registration around 7:30 PM. This is going
                                    to be a very quick, punch
                                    line presentation on your idea to other teams. This presentation is to avoid
                                    confusions among other teams if they ended up thinking the same idea as of yours.
                                </li>
                                <li>
                                    <strong>Concept Presentation</strong> &ndash; You will present the concept on
                                    Saturday the 10th Sept between 8:30 AM to 10:00 AM. There may be eliminations if found the
                                    idea is copied or not complying with the theme. You can always rethink a new one, it means,
                                    the idea could be rejected but teams can go back to their drawing boards.
                                </li>
                                <li>
                                    <strong>Demo Day</strong> &ndash; You will demo your app / product on Monday the
                                    10th Sept in front of all our colleagues. And they are going to vote to show their
                                    love.
                                    Note: Audience vote accounts for 30% of the total score. The Voting will be
                                    anonymous.
                                </li>
                            </ul>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
